 IoT-Based Fire Detection System

 Problem Statement:
Fire accidents cause major property loss and endanger lives due to the lack
of early warning systems in homes and small offices. 

 Objective:
Develop an intelligent fire detection system using gas and temperature sensors
that alert users with a local buzzer alarm  and instant mobile notifications 
 catching danger before it spreads! 

 Hardware & Software Requirements:
  Arduino Uno or NodeMCU
  MQ-2 Gas/Smoke Sensor (detects smoke, LPG, CO)
  DHT11 Temperature Sensor
  Buzzer (local alarm)
  LEDs (visual warning indicators)
  Blynk or IFTTT for phone alerts & notifications

 How It Works:
1 MQ-2 sensor continuously monitors air for smoke and gas 
2 DHT11 tracks ambient temperature for abnormal spikes 
3 If dangerous levels are detected , the buzzer and LEDs activate instantly
4 Simultaneously, a push notification is sent to the user's phone 

 Expected Outcome:
A working prototype that activates local alarms and sends real-time alerts
to the user's phone when fire or gas is detected   providing early
warning that can save lives and property! 

 Technologies Used: Arduino/NodeMCU | MQ-2 | DHT11 | Blynk/IFTTT | IoT Cloud | C++

